headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 29 points, Bennedict Mathurin scored 16 of his 23 points in the fourth quarter and the Indiana Pacers rallied from an 11-point deficit in the final six minutes to beat the short-handed Dallas Mavericks 135-131 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam scores 29 points, has key late steal to help Pacers rally past Mavs 135-131

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 26 points, Alperen Sengun had 22 points and 12 rebounds, and the Houston Rockets extended their winning streak to a season-best eight games, beating the Orlando Magic 116-108 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green and Sengun lead Rockets to season-best 8th straight win, 116-108 over Magic

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham banked in a 3-pointer with less than a second remaining, giving the Detroit Pistons a 116-113 win over Miami on Wednesday night and sending the Heat to their ninth consecutive loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham banks in a 3 for the win and Pistons send Heat to their 9th straight loss, 116-113

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 29 points and CJ McCollum added 18 for New Orleans as the Pelicans surprised the Minnesota Timberwolves with a 119-115 win on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson scores 29 as Pelicans defeat Timberwolves 119-115 in rare road win

headlines.description: — Jaylin Williams scored a career-high 19 points and had 17 rebounds and 11 assists for his second career triple-double, and the Oklahoma City Thunder cruised past the injury-depleted Philadelphia 76ers 133-100 on Wednesday night with Shai...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaylin Williams' triple-double helps short-handed Thunder cruise past 76ers 133-100

events.name: New York Knicks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Sandro Mamukelashvili scored a career-high 34 points on 13-for-14 shooting in 19 minutes to become the first player in NBA history to score 34 points while playing less than 20 minutes as the San Antonio Spurs upended the New York Knicks 120-105 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Mamukelashvili makes NBA history with 34 points in 19 minutes to fuel Spurs' 120-105 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Kyle Filipowski scored 21 points, Keyonte George added 20 and the Utah Jazz snapped a season-worst 10-game skid with a 128-112 victory over the Washington Wizards on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Filipowski and George help Jazz end 10-game skid with 128-112 win over Wizards

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 31 points, nine rebounds and seven assists in just three quarters of work, and the Los Angeles Lakers routed the Denver Nuggets 120-108 on Wednesday night in a matchup of <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 31 after a big 1st quarter, and the Lakers rout the depleted Nuggets 120-108

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 41 points, including 20 in the fourth quarter, and the Phoenix Suns held off the Chicago Bulls 127-121 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 41 to lead Phoenix past Chicago 127-121

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Deni Avdija had 31 points, 16 rebounds and eight assists to lead the Portland Trail Blazers to a 115-99 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers beat Grizzlies 115-99 behind big game from Avdija

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 27 points and the short-handed Sacramento Kings handed the Cleveland Cavaliers their third straight loss with a 123-119 victory on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: The Kings hand the Cavaliers their 3rd straight loss with a 123-119 win
